<title>JAPAN: Daiwa Bank (Trust Account) reveals problem loans.</title>
<headline>Daiwa Bank (Trust Account) reveals problem loans.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Daiwa Bank Ltd has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Mar 97     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans		5.4	     18.6</p>
<p>  Bad loans			   2.8		4.1</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	    8.7	     10.4</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	    16.9	     33.1</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more.</p>
</text>
